// Sized to fit inside LA's validated 512 MiB RAM window (0x9000_0000..
// 0xB000_0000) while leaving enough frames for mmap3's working set: 256 MiB
// heap + ~16 MiB kernel image leaves ~240 MiB of frames, and mmap3 needs both
// ~160 MiB of heap (tmpfs files) AND ~160 MiB of frames (the MAP_SHARED page
// copies) at peak. Going higher requires first confirming real RAM via the DTB
// (see docs/memory-region-dtb.md) — do not bump past what 512 MiB can hold.
